<title>USA: Novell to cut 15 pct of European staff - WSJ.</title>
<headline>Novell to cut 15 pct of European staff - WSJ.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-05-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>Novell Inc. plans to cut about 15 percent of its European work force, representing about 50 jobs, the Wall Street Journal said on Thursday.</p>
<p>In its electronic edition, the Journal said the cuts come amid reports that the network software company was planning a 20 percent reduction in its worldwide work force of 5,800 employees.</p>
<p>The Journal cited Computer Reseller News in its report. The newspaper said Novell declined to comment on the European job cuts.</p>
<p>Novell was not immediately available for comment.</p>
